{
  "texts": [
    "KeynessAnalysis.",
    "Keyness analysis aims to identify terms that stand out while comparing corpora.",
    "In corpus linguistics, the compared corpora are referred to as reference corpus (R) and target corpus (T).",
    "This analysis is performed by measuring whether the frequency of a term in the target corpus stands out statistically compared to its frequency in the reference corpus.",
    "In other words, the null hypothesis 𝐻 0 is defined as there being no difference between the frequency of a term in the compared corpora."
  ]
}